&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Summary:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Neurodiagnostic Education Content Creator is responsible for the development and maintenance of all clinical education content for Cadwell’s EEG product line. This role creates high-quality, customer-facing and internal training materials that reflect Cadwell’s standards for clarity, consistency, and clinical accuracy. Working closely with the Clinical Education Specialist, Manager of Education and Training, and cross-functional teams, this role ensures educational content aligns with product updates, clinical workflows, and company objectives. While EEG will be the primary area of focus initially, this role will also support content development across other neurodiagnostic modalities (IONM, PSG, and EDX/US). Success in this role is measured through content quality, consistency, timely delivery, stakeholder satisfaction, and additional key performance indicators as defined.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Duties / Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop, maintain, and update clinical education content to ensure accuracy, consistency, and alignment with Cadwell branding and educational strategy.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create and update training materials in support of new product releases and software updates, ensuring timely and effective content delivery.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with Clinical Education Specialists to ensure content reflects real-world clinical workflows and best practices.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with other content creators to ensure consistent instructional design, terminology, and delivery standards.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish and maintain standardized formatting, structure, and tone across all internal and customer-facing educational materials.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with internal teams (Education, Product, Sales, Marketing, and Support) to ensure training content reflects consistent messaging and clinical workflows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Gather and incorporate feedback from internal teams and customers to continuously improve educational materials.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support onboarding and provide content orientation for new educators and cross-functional contributors.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with content development across other modalities as needed to support team priorities.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify opportunities to enhance content delivery through new formats (e.g., e-learning, video, simulations, automations, and blended learning).&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure all educational materials comply with regulatory, quality, and branding standards.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to educational initiatives that support customer success and product adoption.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Escalate concerns or workflow gaps to the Manager of Education and Training promptly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform other duties as assigned to support educational operations and organizational goals.&lt;/li&gt;
